<h1>Import / Export</h1>

<% if (error) { %><div class="warning"><%= error %></div><% } %>
<% if (csvErrors) { %>
  <div class="warning">
    <strong>The CSV file has <%= csvErrors.length %> problem<%= csvErrors.length === 1 ? '' : 's' %> — nothing was imported:</strong>
    <ul>
      <% csvErrors.forEach(function(e) { %><li><%= e %></li><% }) %>
    </ul>
  </div>
<% } %>
<% if (result) { %>
  <div class="warning">Import complete — <%= result.creatures %> creature(s), <%= result.buyers %> buyer(s) created or updated.</div>
<% } %>
<% if (csvReport) { %>
  <div class="warning">
    <strong>CSV import finished — <%= csvReport.successCount %> monster(s) created or updated<%= csvReport.failures.length ? ', ' + csvReport.failures.length + ' failed' : '' %>.</strong>
    <% if (csvReport.failures.length) { %>
      <p>These monsters were skipped (everything else in the file was still imported):</p>
      <ul>
        <% csvReport.failures.forEach(function(f) { %><li><%= f.name %> — <%= f.error %></li><% }) %>
      </ul>
      <p>Fix the issue (e.g. seed a missing reference) and re-run the same file — already-imported monsters will just be updated, not duplicated.</p>
    <% } %>
  </div>
<% } %>

<h2>Export</h2>
<p>All exports are local file downloads — nothing leaves this server.</p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="<%= basePath %>/import-export/json">Full JSON export</a> (creatures, components, signature tables, buyers)</li>
  <li><a href="<%= basePath %>/import-export/monsters.csv">Monster list (CSV)</a></li>
  <li><a href="<%= basePath %>/import-export/inventory.csv">Material inventory (CSV)</a></li>
</ul>
<p>For a full database backup (every table, not just creatures/buyers), use <code>npm run db:backup</code> on the server.</p>

<h2>Import monsters (CSV)</h2>
<p>
  <a href="<%= basePath %>/import-export/monsters-template.csv">Download the template CSV</a> —
  it includes a worked example (Wolf and its 4 components) showing the format described below.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>One row = one component.</strong> A monster with several components spans several rows;
  repeat the Monster/Level/Size/etc. columns identically on every row for that monster — only the
  <em>first</em> row for a given Monster Name is actually read for those columns, so an accidental
  difference on a later row is silently ignored rather than causing an error. Leave every
  <code>Component …</code> column blank on a row to import a monster with no component from that row
  (e.g. a monster with zero components yet).
</p>
<p>
  Re-importing the same file is safe to repeat — monsters and components are matched and updated by
  name, not duplicated. Harvest tags, skills, and hazard types referenced by name must already exist
  in this database (seeded by <code>npm run db:seed</code>, or visible on the relevant admin pages).
  Signature tables (e.g. the Black Dragon's Acid Sac row) can't be created via this CSV — use the
  full JSON import or the UI for those.
</p>
<p>
  Each monster is imported in its own transaction, so on a large file one bad row only skips that
  monster — it doesn't roll back everything else. Skipped monsters are listed after the import
  finishes; fix the underlying issue and re-run the same file to pick up just those.
</p>

<form method="post" action="<%= basePath %>/import-export/monsters.csv" id="csv-import-form">
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>" />
  <label>CSV file
    <input type="file" id="csv-import-file-input" accept=".csv,text/csv" />
  </label>
  <textarea name="csvData" id="csv-import-data" style="display:none;"></textarea>
  <button type="submit" id="csv-import-submit" disabled>Import monsters</button>
</form>

<details>
  <summary>CSV column reference (<%= fieldDocs.length %> columns)</summary>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Column</th><th>Level</th><th>Required</th><th>Type / allowed values</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% fieldDocs.forEach(function(f) { %>
        <tr>
          <td><code><%= f.header %></code></td>
          <td><%= f.level %></td>
          <td><%= f.required === true ? 'Yes' : (f.required === false ? 'No' : f.required) %></td>
          <td><%= f.type %></td>
          <td><%= f.description %></td>
        </tr>
      <% }) %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</details>

<h2>Import full data (JSON)</h2>
<p>
  Re-importing a previously exported JSON file is safe to repeat — creatures
  and buyers are matched and updated by name, not duplicated. Reference data
  (skills, harvest tags, hazard types, etc.) must already exist in this
  database (it's seeded by <code>npm run db:seed</code>), since components
  and signature rows are matched to it by name.
</p>
<form method="post" action="<%= basePath %>/import-export/json" id="import-form">
  <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>" />
  <label>JSON file
    <input type="file" id="import-file-input" accept="application/json" />
  </label>
  <textarea name="jsonData" id="import-json-data" style="display:none;"></textarea>
  <button type="submit" id="import-submit" disabled>Import</button>
</form>

<script src="<%= basePath %>/js/import-file.js"></script>
